        IInsertSelectBuilder withInsertHint(boolean withInsertHint)

        this

      • withParallelDml

        IInsertSelectBuilder withParallelDml(boolean useParallelDml)
        Use parallel DML when executing this statement (Oracle only). This behavior may be turned off globally in the configuration by setting the ora-parallel-dml attribute on the upgrade element to "disable". It may also be overridden with the parallel-dml attribute of the versiontrigger element.
        Parameters:
        useParallelDml - whether to use Oracle parallel DML when executing this statement.
        Returns:
        this

      • execute

        int execute()
        Executes the query. If already in a transaction, the query executes in that transaction; otherwise a new transaction is created and committed when the method returns, or rolled back if the method throws an exception. The statement that is constructed will perform default behavior for the following fields (if present and not mapped):- ID (keyable beans only): using new keys from the KeyGenerator PublicID (keyable beans only): default public id prefix followed by a ':' followed by the numeric ID BeanVersion (versionable beans only): 0 CreateTime (editable beans only): current time CreateUser (editable beans only): the current user UpdateTime (editable beans only): current time UpdateUser (editable beans only): the current user Retired (retireable beans only): 0 Columns with default values that are not mapped will be inserted with their default values.
        Returns:
        the number of rows affected
